image.altText: a family walks in the park in Stirling Square surrounded by Sugar Gum trees

props.synopsis: Planted to mark Queen Victoria's Jubilee in 1897, Guildford fought to save its beloved sugar gum trees for the next 100 years. Now, the town celebrates its win each year.

image.altText: Reanna Haswell standing in her front garden with her hands in her pocket.

title.children: Reanna hasn't been able to drink her tap water for years, and she's sceptical a promised solution will eventuate
